Me: So. What have you been up to?

Facilyn wraps the string of her teabag once around her finger, thinking.

Facilyn: Moving. Listening. Arguing with very well-meaning people.

Facilyn: I’ve been traveling a lot since we last saw each other. Different cities. Different cultures. Same pattern.

She looks down into her cup.

Facilyn: People trying. Really trying. Working late. Designing policies. Building tools.

She looks back up.

Facilyn: And still... the problems multiply faster than the solutions.

Facilyn: The polycrisis isn’t a streak of bad luck. It’s not a few broken systems.

Her voice softens slightly.

Facilyn: It’s the result of how we’ve been managing things for centuries.

