@what_complexity
title: What do you mean by "complexity"?
tags: better_way

Facilyn nods slowly.

Facilyn: Let’s start simple.

She gestures vaguely toward the harbour.

Facilyn: A ship. A crane. A drone.

Facilyn: Those are complicated. Many parts. Clear connections. If something breaks, you isolate it, repair it, restart.

Facilyn: Complex systems are different. They’re alive. They adapt. They can not be stopped.

Facilyn: Remember what happened when we thought artificial intelligence was just complicated?

